node.text:
Cocktail of the Day by @monkeymash_lx⁠
.⁠
Name:⁠
Bᴀᴛᴜᴄᴀᴅᴀ ɴᴏ Lᴇʙʟᴏɴ⁠
.⁠
.⁠
Ingredients:⁠
— Leblon⁠
— Pisco 1615 Acholado⁠
— Morango / Strawberry⁠
— Goji⁠
— Folha de Figo / Fig Leaf⁠
[frutado.citrico | fruty.sour] .⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
\\ The consumption of Caçhaca and pisco in Portugal are mainly in the Cocktails caipirinha and pisco sour, which sometimes makes the worlds to explore on the return of these two ingredients is very unexplored. The intention was to create something out of the ordinary and being the first cocktail to be shown of the future "Colors Menu" has the affection of Sustainability and zero waste. The leaves of Fig are harvested in central Portugal near Sertã, in a local environment almost in the wild, all matter of strawberries and goji and reused for decoration.⁠
The highball is elaborated in "Build" mode with only one ice block!⁠
.⁠
.⁠

Cocktail of the Day by @ranvanongevalle⁠
⁠
Ingredients:⁠
Tequila Reposado⁠
Caraway⁠
1976 Vintage Port⁠
⁠
Description:⁠
For our “new classics” section in the new bar, we are playing around with familiar recipes and styles while using uncommon combinations. Here is a simple old-fashioned formula where we gently blend some caraway in our drink(the delicious Doppio Carvi. Beautiful play between the oaky notes from the tequila and the herbacious tones of the caraway. To finish off, we add the smallest bit of some vintage port that, due to oxidation, will add dry and herbal tone that will connect these two ingredients beautifully. Garnishing with a slightly pickled radish and you have a play of taste and aroma that is truly pleasant.⁠
⁠
⁠
⁠
